The #Giants rank at the top of the league in 10+ yard runs, but at the bottom of the league in 15+ yard passes

Thought I'd knock this same plot out for the #NFL 𝗿𝘂𝗻𝗻𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗯𝗮𝗰𝗸𝘀 while I was at it.

Players with a ⬆️ 𝗰𝘂𝗺𝘂𝗹𝗮𝘁𝗶𝘃𝗲 𝗘𝗣𝗔 are shown in the top rows.

Chubb and Jacobs the clear standouts, and its a massive shame about Breece Hall.

#Steelers marks in Week 7 in terms of YAC and EPA. 

Data indicating that George Pickens does not have a lot of separation but certainly generates value when ball is in his hands. Similar to Freiermuth.

#nflverse https://t.co/m08b8RFJnE

Day 2 (2/2): I expected more variance between players (especially at WR since they catch more passes), but the very top performers seem to be the best regardless of scoring system used.
#100daysofcoding #nflverse

Formations snap counts!! KC offense here. No surprises here. Our offense was outstanding. Only 22 personnel wasn't massively in the green. We passed 90% out of 11. That might be a season high? Moore still only getting snaps in 3 WR sets. 

#nflverse #rstats #gtExtras https://t.co/phk5uYtG3k

Defense. We had 5+ on the field for all but 19% of the snaps. Oddly, given how effective they were early running the ball, they passed 73% of the time. Reminder: Dunlap is officially listed as a LB, so make the mental adjustments necessary. 

#nflverse #rstats #gtExtras https://t.co/ftcr5qjEeH

Here's the numbers for San Francisco. They were reasonably effective with 2 RB's or 2 TE's on the field. Those were also the formations they ran out of the most. 

#nflverse #rstats #gtExtras https://t.co/LelfBow5nr
